Pinus oocarpa var. ochoterenai

    Authority
      Family    Pinopsida:Pinaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 8646

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   An evergreen tree reching a height of up to 40 m and a trunk diameter
   up to 80 cm.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. The tree withstands 4-6 months of drought.
   COMMON NAMES
   Ocote de carretilla, Ocote, Shatoj.
   FURTHER INF
   Ocote de carretilla occurs in southern Mexico in the state of Chiapas
   at elevations about 1600-2700 m. The tree is found on flat ground and
   on gentle slopes.

   Sources
   SOURCES (P. oocarpa var. ochoterenai Martinez)
   Serrano C 1978 pp 27-29 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, FER, PH, DRA, DEP]
   Morandini R 1961 pp 132 [RAIN]

